# Portfolio project rules

- Read `README_FIRST.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and relevant PRDs before implementation.
- Do not copy Adam Durrant's exact code, assets, measurements, branding, or copy.
- Use latest stable Next.js App Router and TypeScript.
- Prefer server components.
- Do not make an entire route tree client-rendered.
- Use local MDX and typed data; no database for MVP.
- Do not add paid services.
- Do not invent professional claims, metrics, dates, or testimonials.
- Treat employer and client information as confidential unless explicitly approved.
- Use semantic HTML and target WCAG 2.2 AA.
- Respect reduced motion.
- Maintain visible focus styles.
- Ensure reflow at 320px.
- Keep teal as a restrained accent.
- Avoid purple gradients, glassmorphism, floating blobs, excessive rounded cards, fake terminals, typewriter effects, animated skill bars, random pills, and decorative stock photos.
- Keep dependencies minimal and explain every new package.
- Store content outside reusable components.
- Validate content at build time.
- Run lint, type-check, relevant tests, and production build before declaring completion.
- Return exact files changed, tests run, failures, and unresolved risks.
